Summary
The historical data of SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust (SPY) for the year of 2022 was used to develop the
equaon. Inially the data was loaded, the date column was converted from Object class to
DateTime class, and the summary stascs were checked.
As all columns have signicant standard deviaon greater than 0, we can use all the columns for
equaon. Then Intraday Volality which is equal to (High-Low)/Close along with daily volume
change and daily volality change were calculated and ploed.
We can see that, The volality delta value ranges from 0 to 0.05. Before building the equaons,
correlaon plot was ploed to check the inuence of variables.
We can see that volume has the highest inuence of 0.71 on volality which means if volume
increases the volality increases. Other variables have mild negave correlaon meaning if
Volality increases the other decreases. Linear Regression was used to build the mul variate
linear equaons using Volume, High, Low and Close.
Case 1: Using Equaon built using SPY on other ETFs and Stocks:
With the above built equaon, the Volality values predicted, and percentage of error was
calculated which is the absolute dierence between predicted and actual value divided by the
actual mes 100. Which gives the change between actual and predicted value. The actual and
predicted value were ploed.
From the plot we can say that the equaons t good for given data. The coecients and intercept
are of small value because the variables ranges are big whereas volality is always less than 1.
This equaon is then used on the same data but for 5 Year interval and its Percentage Error and
scaer plot were calculated and ploed.
The same equaon is ploed for other ETFs QQQ Invesco QQQ Trust Series I and VEA Vanguard
FTSE Developed Markets ETF and Stocks Google and Microso respecvely and the results were
noted down.
QQQ
VEA
GOOG
MSFT
Results
We can see the equaon could not represent the actual value well and the mean percentage error
increases with dierent data. This might be since the equaon was largely inuenced by variable
Volume, if it was not as same SPY data then variaons in representaon arises and since the
volality in the dataset with which the equaon was built had values ranging from 0 to 0.06 values
with volality above them were represented accurately and if the data had small values, then also
the representaon produced by the equaon is wrong. The mean percentage error is small if the
data has similar values compared to SPY data. Another Shortcoming of this equaon is using
dependent variables such as High, Low, Close which had high dependencies within them.
